I love the rainbows that appear after a summer shower in my garden. The sky turns grey, then brightens as the sun peeks through the clouds. Suddenly, a beautiful arc stretches across the blue.

It is not just one colour, but many. Red, orange, yellow, green, blue, indigo, and violet. They look like a giant bridge made of light. I imagine fairies dancing on it, or perhaps a giant slide for the clouds.

My favourite part is when the rainbow is very clear. It feels like a secret message from the sky. It tells us that the rain has stopped and the sun is back. Sometimes, if I am lucky, I see two rainbows at once. The second one is fainter, like a quiet echo of the first.

I never try to find the end of the rainbow. I know there is no pot of gold there. Instead, I just stand and smile. The colours make my heart feel warm and happy. It is a special magic that belongs to everyone, free for all to see. [end of text]


